      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/85/17",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ اَلرَّجُلُ يَخْرُجُ فِي تِجَارَةٍ إِلَى مَكَّةَ أَوْ يَكُونُ لَهُ إِبِلٌ فَيُكْرِيهَا حَجَّتُهُ نَاقِصَةٌ أَوْ تَامَّةٌ قَالَ «لاَ بَلْ حَجَّتُهُ تَامَّةٌ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2880 - It was narrated from Mu'awiyah ibn Ammar, who said:\nI said to Abu Abdullah (as): \"A man travels for trade to Mecca or has camels that he rents out. Is his Hajj considered incomplete or complete?\"\nImam (as) said: \"No, rather his Hajj is complete.\""
        ]
      }
    },
